---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Adjunct Faculty | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="Meet Brenkley Doctoral College's Adjunct Faculty — experienced practitioner-scholars from partner institutions who contribute to supervision, teaching, and the Annual Doctoral Symposium.">

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">

      <a href="/supervisors" class="text-accent hover:underline text-sm mb-8 inline-block">&larr; Back to Supervisors</a>

      <p class="section-label mb-4">The Team</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Adjunct Faculty</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl mb-12">Brenkley Doctoral College's Adjunct Faculty are experienced practitioner-scholars from partner institutions who contribute to supervision, methods teaching, and the Annual Doctoral Symposium.</p>

      <div class="space-y-8">

        <div class="card">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-1">Dr Paul G. Oliver</h2>
          <p class="text-accent font-medium text-sm mb-4">Lecturer in Digital Innovation and Entrepreneurship, Edinburgh Napier University</p>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Dr Paul G. Oliver is a Lecturer in Digital Innovation and Entrepreneurship at Edinburgh Napier University, with more than sixteen years of experience in higher education spanning teaching, research, academic leadership and enterprise engagement. He holds degrees in Business and Management and Contemporary Popular Music, together with a PhD in Creative Entrepreneurship. His research focuses on digital transformation, entrepreneurship and innovation within the creative industries, with particular expertise in platformisation, responsible artificial intelligence, algorithmic bias, data governance, entrepreneurial learning and intellectual property management. Dr Oliver has published extensively in internationally recognised peer-reviewed journals and edited books, presented his work at leading international conferences, and actively engages with industry to ensure that his research informs both academic scholarship and professional practice. His interdisciplinary approach bridges technology, entrepreneurship and the creative economy, making him a recognised contributor to contemporary debates on digital innovation, AI and the future of entrepreneurial ecosystems.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-1">Dr Xiaoling Wu</h2>
          <p class="text-accent font-medium text-sm mb-4">Lecturer, Business School, Edinburgh Napier University</p>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Dr Xiaoling Wu is a Lecturer in the Business School at Edinburgh Napier University, specialising in entrepreneurship, innovation, digital transformation and data governance. Her teaching and research focus on the application of emerging technologies, responsible artificial intelligence, digital innovation ecosystems and the governance of data within public and private sector organisations. She contributes to undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral education while supervising research students and engaging in interdisciplinary research that addresses contemporary business and societal challenges. Dr Wu's work combines academic scholarship with practical impact, collaborating with industry and public sector partners to explore how digital technologies can drive innovation, organisational performance and sustainable economic development.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-1">Dr Premnath K. Narayanan</h2>
          <p class="text-accent font-medium text-sm mb-4">Researcher, Educator and Technology Leader — Artificial Intelligence &amp; Digital Transformation</p>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Dr Premnath K. Narayanan is an experienced researcher, educator and technology leader specialising in artificial intelligence, machine learning, digital transformation and advanced computing. He holds a PhD in Computing and has developed expertise across AI, large language models (LLMs), retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), machine learning engineering and digital innovation. His research and professional interests focus on the practical application of AI to solve complex business and organisational challenges, bridging academic research with industry practice. Dr Narayanan is an active contributor to the international AI community through publications, conference presentations and thought leadership, with a particular interest in responsible AI, future technologies, quantum computing, and the impact of artificial intelligence on business, education and society.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-1">Dr Stefanie Schuster</h2>
          <p class="text-accent font-medium text-sm mb-4">Researcher and Industry Practitioner — Business, Management &amp; Organisational Development</p>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Dr Stefanie Schuster is an experienced researcher and industry practitioner with expertise in business, management, organisational development and applied research. Rather than pursuing a traditional academic career, she has built her professional reputation through leadership and management practice, bringing extensive real-world experience into research, supervision and professional development. She has supported postgraduate and doctoral students in developing rigorous research that is grounded in practical application and organisational impact. Her professional interests include organisational leadership, innovation, strategic management and research methodology, with a strong commitment to interdisciplinary collaboration, evidence-based practice and translating research into meaningful organisational outcomes. Dr Schuster has participated in international research projects and professional networks, combining scholarly knowledge with extensive practitioner experience to promote innovation, critical thinking and knowledge exchange between higher education and industry.</p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-primary">Enquire about supervision</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
